\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1910858 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3764008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 Any hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1910858 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3764008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 How many times a week would you eat meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1910858 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 Well, I think we'd have a bit nearly every day. If it were - if it were - if you call ham or bacon or - we'd always a - chops or st
eak and - and a joint - you know, we had meat I should say five times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3764008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1910858 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1538111\charrsid13597434 No. Oh we might have had corned beef. Yes. In war we started with corned beef, we used to make pies with it.
